## Data Science 


## Emmanuel Ezenwekwe


### python guide 
*python* Python is a readable programming language for data, web, AI. Install from python.org, verify with python --version. Use variables (str, int, float, bool), math operators, lists, dicts, tuples, sets. Control with if/else, for/while loops. Define functions, import modules like math/random. Handle errors.

### marimo summary 
*marimo*Marimo Reactive Python notebook as .py files. Features: auto-updates, git-friendly, no hidden state, UI widgets. Install via uv, run with uv run marimo edit file.py. Cells: code/Markdown, reactive execution. Export to HTML/Python. Best for reproducible data work over Jupyter.
### git summary 
*git* Git Version control for tracking file changes,config name/email. Init repo with git init or clone. Workflow: git status, add file/., commit -m "msg". View log/show. Undo with restore. Branches: create/switch/merge/delete. Remotes: push/pull to GitHub.
### plotly summary
*Plotly* Interactive charts library. Use px.scatter/line/bar/histogram/box/pie with Polars DataFrames. Customize colors/themes/labels/legends/hover. Subplots/dashboards via make_subplots. Export HTML/image. Works in Marimo. Start with px for quick viz.
### polars summary 
*polars* is an open-source DataFrame library for fast data manipulation and analytical queries. Written in Rust, it uses the Apache Arrow columnar memory model to achieve high performance and efficient parallelism. It is widely adopted as a modern alternative to pandas for large-scale data processing.
### vscode-guide.md
*vscode*is a free code editor by Microsoft used to write and manage code.
It works like a powerful text editor but includes tools that understand programming.
### uv-package-management.md
*uv-package*is a modern Python package manager built in Rust by Astral.
It manages packages, Python versions, and virtual environments in one tool.
### what is Data science
Data science turns raw data into useful information.
### mark down writing 
Markdown is a simple plain-text formatting system that uses symbols (like #, *, and []) to control how text appears when displayed. It lets you create formatted documents headings, lists, links, images, and code without needing formatting buttons.
